'''''Better with You'''''  <!-- Do not change -->is<!-- to "was" as that is incorrect per [[WP:TVLEAD]]. Fiction continues to exist even after creation of new episodes stops.--> an [[Television in the United States|American]] [[romantic comedy|romantic]] [[sitcom]] TV show starring [[Joanna Garcia|Joanna Garcia Swisher]] and [[Jennifer Finnigan]].  The series aired on Wednesdays at 8:30 pm Eastern/7:30 pm Central on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] and ran from September 22, 2010 to May 11, 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/05/abcs-fall-tv-schedule-night-by-night.html |title=ABC's fall TV schedule, night by night|author=Hanh Nguyen |date=May 18, 2010|work=[[Zap2it]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=May 18, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/special/fall-preview/fall-schedule.aspx|title=Fall 2010 Day-By-Day TV Schedule|publisher=TVGuide.com}}</ref><ref>[http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/07/08/abc-announces-fall-series-premiere-dates/56502 ABC Announces Fall Series Premiere Dates], ''TV By the Numbers'', July 8, 2010</ref> 

The series was officially cancelled on May 13, 2011 by ABC.<ref>[http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/05/13/better-with-you-cancelled-by-abc/92569/]</ref>

==Plot==
The series revolved around three different relationships that are tightly intertwined in one family, as it follows a couple, Maddie and Ben, who had been dating for nine years and are happy just [[Cohabitation|living together]] despite not taking the next step, marriage. Maddie's life is thrown for a loop when her younger sister Mia announces that she is pregnant and is about to marry Casey, a guy whom she has only known for seven weeks. To make matters worse, Maddie is stunned that their parents, who have been married for 35 years and have their issues, approve of the union, leaving Maddie and Ben questioning themselves about their own relationship.

==Cast==
*[[Joanna Garcia|Joanna Garcia Swisher]] as Mia Putney
*[[Jennifer Finnigan]] as Madeleine "Maddie" Putney
*[[Josh Cooke]] as Ben Coles
*[[Jake Lacy]] as Casey Marion Davenport
*[[Kurt Fuller]] as Joel Putney
*[[Debra Jo Rupp]] as Vicky Putney

==Production==
''Better with You'' was previously known as ''Better Together'', ''Leapfrog'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2009/09/18/development-update-friday-september-18/8300/|title=Development Update: Friday, September 18|date=September 18, 2009|work=The Futon Critic|accessdate=May 23, 2010}}</ref> and then briefly as ''That Couple''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2010/05/13/chuck-v-eight-pilots-make-the-cut-for-2010-11/8670/|title="Chuck", "V," Eight Pilots Make the Cut for 2010-11|date=May 13, 2010|work=The Futon Critic|accessdate=May 20, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediaweek.com/mw/content_display/news/national-broadcast/e3i6478fc41cf5464a5822024680005b756|title=ABC: Seven New Series; Changes Affect Four Nights|last=Berman|first=Marc|date=May 18, 2010|work=Media Week|accessdate=May 23, 2010}}</ref> On January 15, 2010, ABC [[green-light|green-lit]] the [[television pilot|pilot]], which was written by ''[[Friends]]'' writer and [[executive producer]] Shana Goldberg-Meehan and directed by [[James Burrows]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2010/01/15/development-update-friday-january-15/8475/|title=Development Update: Friday, January 15|date=January 15, 2010|work=The Futon Critic|accessdate=May 23, 2010}}</ref> The show was produced by Bonanza Productions, Silver and Gold Productions, and [[Warner Bros. Television]]. ''Better with You'' aired on Wednesday at 8:30 after ''[[The Middle (TV series)|The Middle]]'' and before ''[[Modern Family]]''.<ref>[http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/05/18/abc-announces-2010-11-primetime-schedule/51686 ABC Announces 2010-11 Primetime Schedule], ''TV By the Numbers'', May 18, 2010</ref> On October 26, ABC announced that ''Better with You'' was picked up for a full 22-episode season.<ref>http://news.bostonherald.com/blogs/entertainment/love_that_tv/?p=366&srvc=home&position=recent</ref>

[[Ben Kweller]] wrote the theme song for the show.<ref>http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/11/better-with-you-theme-songs-are-better-with-ben-kweller.html</ref> Country music singer [[Reba McEntire]] made an appearance in episode 8 of season 1, "Better with Flirting," as wedding planner Lorraine Ashley. Series regular Joanna Garcia Swisher and McEntire both starred in the WB/CW series ''[[Reba (TV series)|Reba]]''.

''Better with You'' marked the second time Josh Cooke and Jennifer Finnigan have co-starred on a sitcom, the first being the short-lived 2005 NBC series ''[[Committed (2005 TV series)|Committed]]''; it is also the second time that Cooke and Kurt Fuller co-starred in a sitcom, having previously starred in the short-lived 2007 ABC sitcom ''[[Big Day]]''.

